               <p>Anne Sparks depos'd, That the Goods were brought to her by both the Prisoners, and she bought them of them.</p>
               <p>Hall pleaded, That he had been admitted an Evidence, and therefore ought not to be try'd for this Fact, which was committed before; but it appearing that he had not put this Fact into his Information, his Plea did not avail; and it being plainly prov'd, the Jury found them both <rs id="t17310115-70-verdict351" type="verdictDescription">
